path.desc: Alexandria is by no means self-sufficient, though it has the potential to produce up to 50% of the food it consumes, thanks to the popularization of vertical farms. Widely adopted in modernistic cities such as Delphi, these staggering buildings adopt a mixture of science and magecraft to nurture their crops. Meanwhile, animals that require plenty of lateral space to be comfortable are raised outdoors. There isn’t much excitement in the farming district. Noise levels are kept to a minimum, and all waters running through the district are triple filtered and fresh from the Water District. A slew of research facilities dot the peripherals of the district, where scholars focus on advancing the quality and efficiency of crops and livestock through genetic development.;https://cdn.discordapp.com/emojis/764196119428202516.webp
path.title: Farming District

path.desc: The leisure district is home to many of the older citizens of Alexandria. It is considered to be one of the quietest districts in the city, with plenty of parks and gardens for plant Magecraft enthusiasts to experiment on. The standard of living tends to be higher in this area, as it’s filled with gigantic shopping malls filled with everything a person could ever need. Contrary to its name, the leisure district also houses many of the research institutions in Alexandria, perhaps due to its quiet nature. Warehouses full of tools, utilities and Mystic Codes provide the older folks great assistance in home renovation. It is the perfect location for retirement.;https://cdn.discordapp.com/emojis/764196119428202516.webp
path.title: Leisure District

path.desc: The nightlife district is an offshoot of the cultural and water districts that gained its own identity as time passed, focusing more on housing a robust nightlife scene and indulging in recreational and leisurely activities. During the day, most of the district’s famous buildings are closed or have limited service, but awaken at sunset. It reaches peak hours from dusk to the next morning. The district features a large number of bars, restaurants, nightclubs, and hotels designed to cater to a younger, more active audience. Even the various bookstores, art galleries, and historical festivals have taken a fresh spin under the district’s influence. Alcohol and beverages, especially those imported from other cities, are among the most distributed goods in this area. ;https://cdn.discordapp.com/emojis/764196119428202516.webp
path.title: Nightlife District

path.desc: The water district is responsible for the city’s water supply and sewage disposal. All wastewater from the city’s sewers pass by the water district, where they are filtered and recycled with the aid of Magecraft. 90% of the filth can be purified by powerful purification enchantments alone. The district is also home to gigantic water parks, artificial coastlines and beaches, aquariums, fish markets, and boasts an impressive food scene. Many of the exotic fishes can be found on ordinary restaurant menus here. However, fishing in this area is strictly banned, as the activity may pose a danger to scuba and deep sea divers.;https://cdn.discordapp.com/emojis/764196119428202516.webp
path.title: Water District

path.desc: The cultural district houses the city’s largest scene of museums, galleries, and theaters. Many surviving masterpieces of the Old World have been recovered and restored by librarians or graciously donated by high ranking mages from other cities. A multitude of architectural wonders that are reminiscent of past cultures have also been erected or grafted onto this district. They are often used to host various festivities passed down from ancient traditions, while inviting both locals and foreigners to partake in the joy of knowing the past. These festivals are always popular when held.;https://cdn.discordapp.com/emojis/764196119428202516.webp
path.title: Cultural District

path.desc: Route 934 is a covert delivery network that delivers anything from inconspicuous goods to classified artifacts, documents, and even Servant frames. It masks itself as an average delivery network by delivering both low and high risk items. A smaller district lined with warehouses and shipping centers, it sandwiches itself between the Academy and the Foreigner’s districts. It works with Alexandria’s library network, the major catalyst and artifact vaults, as well as the Church’s embassy, allowing for fast clearance and swift transportation of items once they have set foot in the city.;https://cdn.discordapp.com/emojis/764196119428202516.webp
path.title: Route 934

path.desc: Alexandria has an insatiable thirst for knowledge. It enjoys cultivating relationships with other cities and welcomes them to set up offices in Alexandria. The foreigner’s district is a melting pot of various cultures and inhabitants who are either visiting the city or looking for a new life here. It also houses embassies of many factions, such as the Church, the Mage’s Association and many more.;https://cdn.discordapp.com/emojis/764196119428202516.webp
path.title: Foreigner's District

path.desc: The city center, otherwise known as the academy district, is the area immediately surrounding the Great Library. Many buildings in this district have been fortified by magecraft, with added security from mages and Servants due to their proximity to Alexandria’s golden goose. All roads lead to the academy district, making it home to many of Alexandria’s largest attractions.;https://cdn.discordapp.com/emojis/764196119428202516.webp
path.title: Academy District (City Center)
